Two nurses are seen next to a machine that checks oxygen levels of a patient infected with COVID-19 at ward number 20 of the Tembisa Hospital in Tembisa. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has recorded 1,385 new coronavirus cases in the last 24 hours. That brings the total number of confirmed cases in the country to 1,574,370. Sadly 59 more people have died because of the virus. READ: Vaccine doses pass one billion mark as global cases top new record The total number of COVID-19 related deaths now stands at 54,125 There are 19,885 active cases nationwide. The recovery rate is at 95-percent.